Synopsis: Generates a JSON Web Token (JWT) for a GitHub App.
Description: Generates a JSON Web Token (JWT) for a GitHub App.
Notes: [Generating a JSON Web Token (JWT) for a GitHub App | GitHub Docs](https://docs.github.com/en/apps/creating-github-apps/authenticating-with-a-github-app/generating-a-json-web-token-jwt-for-a-github-app#example-using-powershell-to-generate-a-jwt)

Examples.Title: EXAMPLE 1
Examples.Code:
Get-GitHubAppJWT -ClientId 'Iv987654321' -PrivateKeyFilePath '/path/to/private-key.pem'
Generates a JSON Web Token (JWT) for a GitHub App using the specified client ID and private key file path.

Examples.Title: EXAMPLE 2
Examples.Code:
Get-GitHubAppJWT -ClientId 'Iv987654321' -PrivateKey '--- BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY --- ... --- END RSA PRIVATE KEY ---'
Generates a JSON Web Token (JWT) for a GitHub App using the specified client ID and private key.
